{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1150,"text":"So, I love making tools\nand sharing them with people."},{"time":5118,"text":"I remember as a child,"},{"time":6532,"text":"my first tool I built\nwas actually a microscope"},{"time":9849,"text":"that I built by stealing lenses\nfrom my brother's eyeglasses."},{"time":14289,"text":"He wasn't that thrilled."},{"time":16100,"text":"But, you know, maybe\nbecause of that moment,"},{"time":18294,"text":"30 years later,"},{"time":19471,"text":"I'm still making microscopes."},{"time":22359,"text":"And the reason I built these tools\nis for moments like this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":27559,"text":"(Video) Girl: I have\nblack things in my hair --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":30003,"text":"Manu Prakash: This is a school\nin the Bay Area."}]},{"cues":[{"time":32840,"text":"(Video) MP: The living world\nfar supersedes our imagination"},{"time":37328,"text":"of how things actually work."}]},{"cues":[{"time":39319,"text":"(Video) Boy: Oh my God!"}]},{"cues":[{"time":43773,"text":"MP: Right -- oh my God!"},{"time":46621,"text":"I hadn't realized this would be\nsuch a universal phrase."}]},{"cues":[{"time":51123,"text":"Over the last two years,"},{"time":52947,"text":"in my lab,"},{"time":54138,"text":"we built 50,000 Foldscopes"},{"time":56237,"text":"and shipped them\nto 130 countries in the world,"},{"time":59171,"text":"at no cost to the kids we sent them to."},{"time":62238,"text":"This year alone,"},{"time":63505,"text":"with the support of our community,"},{"time":65661,"text":"we are planning to ship\na million microscopes"},{"time":68165,"text":"to kids around the world."},{"time":70034,"text":"What does that do?"},{"time":71628,"text":"It creates an inspiring community\nof people around the world,"},{"time":75408,"text":"learning and teaching each other,"},{"time":77104,"text":"from Kenya to Kampala\nto Kathmandu to Kansas."}]},{"cues":[{"time":81218,"text":"And one of the phenomenal things\nthat I love about this"},{"time":83887,"text":"is the sense of community."},{"time":85871,"text":"There's a kid in Nicaragua"},{"time":87287,"text":"teaching others how to identify\nmosquito species that carry dengue"},{"time":91505,"text":"by looking at the larva\nunder a microscope."},{"time":93947,"text":"There's a pharmacologist\nwho came up with a new way"},{"time":96519,"text":"to detect fake drugs anywhere."},{"time":99402,"text":"There is a girl who wondered:"},{"time":101485,"text":"\"How does glitter actually work?\""},{"time":103207,"text":"and discovered the physics\nof crystalline formation in glitter."},{"time":107713,"text":"There is an Argentinian doctor"},{"time":109342,"text":"who's trying to do field cervical cancer\nscreening with this tool."},{"time":113628,"text":"And yours very truly found\na species of flea"},{"time":117390,"text":"that was dug inside my heel in my foot\none centimeter deep."}]},{"cues":[{"time":123321,"text":"Now, you might think\nof these as anomalies."},{"time":127975,"text":"But there is a method to this madness."},{"time":130617,"text":"I call this \"frugal science\" --"},{"time":132871,"text":"the idea of sharing\nthe experience of science,"},{"time":136747,"text":"and not just the information."},{"time":139011,"text":"To remind you:"},{"time":140250,"text":"there are a billion people on this planet"},{"time":142358,"text":"who live with absolutely\nno infrastructure:"},{"time":144897,"text":"no roads,"},{"time":146535,"text":"no electricity"},{"time":147941,"text":"and thus, no health care."},{"time":150967,"text":"Also, there a billion kids\non this planet that live in poverty."},{"time":155700,"text":"How are we supposed to inspire them"},{"time":157392,"text":"for the next generation\nof solution makers?"},{"time":160264,"text":"There are health care workers\nthat we put on the line"},{"time":163036,"text":"to fight infectious diseases,"},{"time":164978,"text":"to protect us with absolutely\nbare-minimum tools and resources."}]},{"cues":[{"time":170584,"text":"So as a lab at Stanford,"},{"time":172202,"text":"I think of this from a context\nof frugal science"},{"time":176163,"text":"and building solutions\nfor these communities."},{"time":178772,"text":"Often we think about being able to do\ndiagnosis under a tree, off-grid."},{"time":183816,"text":"I'll tell you two examples\ntoday of new tools."},{"time":186569,"text":"One of them starts in Uganda."},{"time":188751,"text":"In 2013,"},{"time":190304,"text":"on a field trip to detect\nschistosomiasis with Foldscopes,"},{"time":194374,"text":"I made a minor observation."},{"time":196956,"text":"In a clinic,"},{"time":198557,"text":"in a far, remote area,"},{"time":199920,"text":"I saw a centrifuge\nbeing used as a doorstop."},{"time":204192,"text":"I mean -- quite literally, the doorstop."},{"time":206607,"text":"And I asked them and they said,"},{"time":208357,"text":"\"Oh, we don't actually have electricity,"},{"time":210408,"text":"so this piece of junk\nis good as a doorstop.\""},{"time":214624,"text":"Centrifuges, for some of you\nwho don't know,"},{"time":217350,"text":"are the pinnacle tool to be able\nto do sample processing."},{"time":220598,"text":"You separate components\nof blood or body fluids"},{"time":223364,"text":"to be able to detect\nand identify pathogens."},{"time":226419,"text":"But centrifuges are bulky, expensive --"},{"time":229277,"text":"cost around 1,000 dollars --"},{"time":231495,"text":"and really hard to carry out in the field."},{"time":233525,"text":"And of course,"},{"time":234706,"text":"they don't work without power."},{"time":236164,"text":"Sound familiar?"},{"time":237580,"text":"So we started thinking\nabout solving this problem,"},{"time":240152,"text":"and I came back --"},{"time":241726,"text":"kept thinking about toys."}]},{"cues":[{"time":243818,"text":"Now ..."},{"time":246030,"text":"I have a few with me here."},{"time":247812,"text":"I first started with yo-yos ..."},{"time":249943,"text":"and I'm a terrible yo-yo thrower."},{"time":252923,"text":"Because these objects spin,"},{"time":254628,"text":"we wondered,"},{"time":255814,"text":"could we actually use\nthe physics of these objects"},{"time":258195,"text":"to be able to build centrifuges?"},{"time":261257,"text":"This was possibly the worst\nthrow I could make."},{"time":264436,"text":"But you might start realizing,"},{"time":265953,"text":"if you start exploring\nthe space of toys --"},{"time":268816,"text":"we tried these spinning tops,"},{"time":271445,"text":"and then in the lab,"},{"time":273351,"text":"we stumbled upon this wonder."}]},{"cues":[{"time":275770,"text":"It's the whirligig,\nor a buzzer, or a rundle."},{"time":279280,"text":"A couple of strings and a little disk,"},{"time":281721,"text":"and if I push, it spins."},{"time":284350,"text":"How many of you have played\nwith this as a kid?"},{"time":286718,"text":"This is called a button-on-a-string."},{"time":288590,"text":"OK, maybe 50 percent of you."},{"time":290250,"text":"What you didn't realize --"},{"time":291832,"text":"that this little object"},{"time":294169,"text":"is the oldest toy\nin the history of mankind ..."},{"time":299007,"text":"5,000 years ago."},{"time":300676,"text":"We have found relics of this object\nhidden around on our planet."},{"time":305104,"text":"Now the irony is,"},{"time":307069,"text":"we actually don't understand\nhow this little thing works."},{"time":310828,"text":"That's when I get excited."}]},{"cues":[{"time":312797,"text":"So we got back to work,"},{"time":314902,"text":"wrote down a couple of equations."},{"time":317056,"text":"If you take the input torque\nthat you put in,"},{"time":320393,"text":"you take the drag on this disc,"},{"time":322521,"text":"and the twist drag on these strings,"},{"time":324450,"text":"you should be able\nto mathematically solve this."},{"time":326963,"text":"This is not the only equation in my talk."},{"time":329795,"text":"Ten pages of math later,"},{"time":331651,"text":"we could actually write down\nthe complete analytical solution"},{"time":334534,"text":"for this dynamic system."},{"time":336388,"text":"And out comes what we call \"Paperfuge.\""},{"time":340023,"text":"That's my postdoc Saad Bhamla,"},{"time":342591,"text":"who's the co-inventor of Paperfuge."},{"time":344282,"text":"And to the left, you see\nall the centrifuges"},{"time":346551,"text":"that we're trying to replace."}]},{"cues":[{"time":348002,"text":"This little object that you see right here"},{"time":352939,"text":"is a disc, a couple\nof strings and a handle."},{"time":356208,"text":"And when I spin"},{"time":357940,"text":"and I push,"},{"time":359117,"text":"it starts to spin."},{"time":360293,"text":"Now, when you realize,"},{"time":362950,"text":"when you do the math,"},{"time":365579,"text":"when we calculate the rpm for this object,"},{"time":368093,"text":"mathematically, we should be able\nto go all the way to a million rpm."},{"time":372849,"text":"Now, there is a little twist\nin human anatomy,"},{"time":375066,"text":"because the resonant frequency\nof this object is about 10 hertz,"},{"time":378165,"text":"and if you've ever played the piano,"},{"time":379993,"text":"you can't go higher\nthan two or three hertz."},{"time":382111,"text":"The maximum speed we've been able\nto achieve with this object"},{"time":385399,"text":"is not 10,000 rpm,"},{"time":387352,"text":"not 50,000 rpm --"},{"time":388980,"text":"120,000 rpm."},{"time":390929,"text":"That's equal to 30,000 g-forces."},{"time":393757,"text":"If I was to stick you right here\nand have it spin,"},{"time":396988,"text":"you would think about the types\nof forces you would experience."}]},{"cues":[{"time":400441,"text":"One of the factors of a tool like this"},{"time":402703,"text":"is to be able to do diagnosis with this."},{"time":405721,"text":"So, I'm going to do\na quick demo here, where --"},{"time":410442,"text":"this is a moment where I'm going\nto make a little finger prick,"},{"time":414061,"text":"and a tiny drop of blood\nis going to come out."},{"time":416360,"text":"If you don't like blood,\nyou don't have to look at it."},{"time":419005,"text":"Here is a little lancet."},{"time":420368,"text":"These lancets are available everywhere,"},{"time":422262,"text":"completely passive."},{"time":423809,"text":"And if I've had breakfast today ..."},{"time":430047,"text":"That didn't hurt at all."},{"time":431558,"text":"OK, I take a little capillary\nwith a drop of blood --"},{"time":435566,"text":"now this drop of blood has answers,"},{"time":437849,"text":"that's why I'm interested in it."},{"time":439910,"text":"It might actually tell me whether\nI have malaria right now or not."},{"time":443401,"text":"I take a little capillary,"},{"time":445257,"text":"and you see it starts wicking in."},{"time":447888,"text":"I'm going to draw a little more blood."},{"time":452782,"text":"And that's good enough for right now."},{"time":455519,"text":"Now, I just seal this capillary\nby putting it in clay."},{"time":463492,"text":"And now that's sealed the sample."}]},{"cues":[{"time":465796,"text":"We're going to take the sample,"},{"time":467949,"text":"mount it on Paperfuge."},{"time":477092,"text":"A little piece of tape\nto make a sealed cavity."},{"time":480975,"text":"So now the sample is completely enclosed."},{"time":487107,"text":"And we are ready for a spin."},{"time":491019,"text":"I'm pushing and pulling with this object."},{"time":493084,"text":"I'm going to load this up ..."},{"time":496277,"text":"And you see the object starts spinning."},{"time":498584,"text":"Unlike a regular centrifuge,"},{"time":500622,"text":"this is a counter-rotating centrifuge."},{"time":504425,"text":"It goes back and forth, back and forth ..."},{"time":507221,"text":"And now I'm charging it up,"},{"time":509373,"text":"and you see it builds momentum."},{"time":512185,"text":"And now -- I don't know\nif you can hear this --"},{"time":514821,"text":"30 seconds of this,"},{"time":516989,"text":"and I should be able to separate\nall the blood cells with the plasma."},{"time":521938,"text":"And the ratio of those blood \ncells to plasma --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":524775,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":528439,"text":"Already, if you see right here,"},{"time":532206,"text":"if you focus on this,"},{"time":533854,"text":"you should be able to see\na separated volume"},{"time":537272,"text":"of blood and plasma."},{"time":539154,"text":"And the ratio of that actually tells me\nwhether I might be anemic."}]},{"cues":[{"time":543101,"text":"One of the aspects of this is,\nwe build many types of Paperfuges."},{"time":547162,"text":"This one allows us to identify\nmalaria parasites"},{"time":551652,"text":"by running them for a little longer,"},{"time":553493,"text":"and we can identify malaria parasites\nthat are in the blood"},{"time":557083,"text":"that we can separate out and detect\nwith something like a centrifuge."},{"time":560681,"text":"Another version of this allows me\nto separate nucleic acids"},{"time":565185,"text":"to be able to do nucleic acid tests\nout in the field itself."},{"time":569573,"text":"Here is another version that allows me\nto separate bulk samples,"},{"time":573941,"text":"and then, finally,"},{"time":575535,"text":"something new that we've been working on"},{"time":577559,"text":"to be able to implement the entire\nmultiplex test on an object like this."},{"time":582378,"text":"So where you do the sample preparation\nand the chemistry in the same object."}]},{"cues":[{"time":587540,"text":"Now ..."},{"time":588850,"text":"this is all good,"},{"time":590144,"text":"but when you start thinking about this,"},{"time":592075,"text":"you have to share these tools with people."},{"time":594188,"text":"And one of the things we did is --\nwe just got back from Madagascar;"},{"time":597594,"text":"this is what clinical trials\nfor malaria look like --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":600196,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":601223,"text":"You can do this while having coffee."},{"time":603604,"text":"But most importantly,"},{"time":605501,"text":"this is a village six hours from any road."},{"time":610036,"text":"We are in a room with one of the senior\nmembers of the community"},{"time":614623,"text":"and a health care worker."},{"time":616160,"text":"It really is this portion of the work\nthat excites me the most --"},{"time":619681,"text":"that smile,"},{"time":620863,"text":"to be able to share simple but powerful\ntools with people around the world."},{"time":625479,"text":"Now, I forgot to tell you this,"},{"time":627805,"text":"that all of that cost me 20 cents to make."}]},{"cues":[{"time":631510,"text":"OK, in the negative time I have left,"},{"time":634416,"text":"I'll tell you about the most recent --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":636506,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":637650,"text":"invention from our lab."},{"time":639544,"text":"It's called Abuzz --"},{"time":641618,"text":"the idea that all of you\ncould help us fight mosquitoes;"},{"time":645776,"text":"you could all help us track our enemies."},{"time":648067,"text":"These are enemies because they cause\nmalaria, Zika, chikungunya, dengue."},{"time":652079,"text":"But the challenge is that we actually\ndon't know where our enemies are."},{"time":656887,"text":"The world map for where\nmosquitoes are is missing."},{"time":660303,"text":"So we started thinking about this."},{"time":662070,"text":"There are 3,500 species of mosquitoes,"},{"time":664129,"text":"and they're all very similar."},{"time":665556,"text":"Some of them are so identical"},{"time":667019,"text":"that even an entomologist cannot\nidentify them under a microscope."}]},{"cues":[{"time":671096,"text":"But they have an Achilles' heel."},{"time":672905,"text":"This is what mosquitoes flirting\nwith each other looks like."},{"time":676129,"text":"That's a male chasing a female."},{"time":678382,"text":"They're actually talking to each other\nwith their wingbeat frequencies."},{"time":682227,"text":"(Buzzing sound)"},{"time":683291,"text":"And thus, they have a signature."},{"time":686652,"text":"We realized that using a regular phone,"},{"time":690040,"text":"a $5-10 flip phone --"},{"time":692605,"text":"how many remember what this object is?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":694731,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":695815,"text":"We can record these acoustic\nsignatures from mosquitoes."},{"time":700000,"text":"I'll tell you exactly how to do this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":701960,"text":"I caught some mosquitoes outside."},{"time":703675,"text":"Unlike Bill [Gates], I'm not\ngoing to release them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":706087,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":707151,"text":"But I will tell you how\nto record from this."},{"time":709750,"text":"All you do is tap them and they fly."},{"time":712216,"text":"You can first test --"},{"time":713581,"text":"I can actually hear that."},{"time":715357,"text":"And you bring your phone,\nwhich has microphones --"},{"time":717835,"text":"it turns out the mics\nare so damn good already,"},{"time":720225,"text":"even on regular phones,"},{"time":721489,"text":"that you can pick up\nthis near-field signature."},{"time":723946,"text":"And since I'm out of time,"},{"time":726108,"text":"let me just play the recording\nthat I made a day ago."}]},{"cues":[{"time":729824,"text":"(Mosquitoes buzz)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":732388,"text":"This is all the charming sound\nthat you heard before"},{"time":735340,"text":"that you all love."},{"time":738786,"text":"One of the contexts of this"},{"time":740231,"text":"is that being able to do this\nwith a regular cell phone"},{"time":743469,"text":"allows us to map mosquito species."},{"time":747657,"text":"Using a flip phone,"},{"time":749373,"text":"we mapped one of the largest\nacoustic databases"},{"time":752375,"text":"with 25 to 20 species of mosquitoes\nthat carry human pathogens."},{"time":757627,"text":"And from this and machine learning,"},{"time":759330,"text":"anybody who uploads this data,"},{"time":761138,"text":"we can identify and tell the probability"},{"time":763150,"text":"of what species of mosquitoes\nyou're actually working with."},{"time":766008,"text":"We call this Abuzz,\nand if any of you want to sign up,"},{"time":768847,"text":"just go to the website."}]},{"cues":[{"time":770523,"text":"Let me close with something"},{"time":772189,"text":"that's very important\nand dear to my heart."},{"time":775504,"text":"One of the challenges of today\nis we have terrible problems."},{"time":779475,"text":"We have a billion people\nwith absolutely no health care,"},{"time":782397,"text":"climate change, biodiversity loss,"},{"time":784546,"text":"on and on and on."},{"time":786226,"text":"And we hope that science\nis going to provide the answer."}]},{"cues":[{"time":789590,"text":"But before you leave this theatre today,"},{"time":791762,"text":"I want you to promise one thing."},{"time":793925,"text":"We're going to make science accessible --"},{"time":797066,"text":"not just to the people who can afford it,"},{"time":799229,"text":"but a billion others who can't."},{"time":801761,"text":"Let's make science and scientific\nliteracy a human right."},{"time":807564,"text":"The moment that you pass the tingling\nfeeling of making a discovery"},{"time":812263,"text":"to another child,"},{"time":814443,"text":"you're enabling them to be\nthe next group of people"},{"time":818259,"text":"who will actually solve these problems."}]},{"cues":[{"time":820391,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":821590,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}